# 9Ô∏è‚É£ PERFORMANCE IMPACT ON FUTURE PROCUREMENT

Performance influences:

---

## üîπ A. Supplier Discovery (Logic 5)

Matching algorithm prioritizes:

* Higher-rated suppliers
* Reliable performers
* Low dispute history

---

## üîπ B. Evaluation Framework (Logic 8)

Performance history can be:

* Mandatory eligibility threshold
* Scored criterion (e.g., 10‚Äì20%)
* Risk adjustment factor

---

## üîπ C. Risk Escalation (Logic 11)

Low-rated supplier ‚Üí additional approval scrutiny.

---

# üîü CORRECTIVE ACTION & SANCTIONS

If performance falls below threshold:

System may trigger:

* Warning notice
* Mandatory corrective action plan
* Temporary suspension
* Restricted bidding eligibility
* Full blacklisting (with approval)

All actions logged under Logic 14.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ DISPUTE & APPEAL FAIRNESS

Supplier can:

* View performance evaluation
* Submit rebuttal
* Provide corrective evidence
* Appeal rating decision

System must:

* Log evaluator identity
* Record justification
* Prevent anonymous rating

Ensures fairness and avoids abuse.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ EARLY WARNING SYSTEM

Real-time monitoring triggers alerts if:

* Delivery delay exceeds threshold
* SLA breach frequency high
* Quality defects increasing
* Communication response time deteriorates

Allows intervention before contract failure.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ PERFORMANCE TREND ANALYSIS

System tracks:

* Performance trajectory over time
* Category-based improvement/decline
* Risk patterns across projects
* Supplier reliability index

Supports strategic sourcing decisions.

